lavery. Moneylending practices and the formation of servile conditions at Emar are studied in the context of the Syrian economy aiming to understand whether the Emar evidence conforms with a socio political and economic crisis that is generally acknowledged to have struck Syria, Anatolia and Northern Mesopotamia at the end of the Late Bronze Age. This work is of sure relevance for scholars interested in socio-economic history, not only of the pertinent historical-geographical area.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCreditzSyriazEmar (Extinct city) 0aCreditzSyriazEmar (Extinct city). 0aDebtzSyriazEmar (Extinct city) 0aDebtzSyriazEmar (Extinct city). 0aEmar (Extinct city)xEconomic conditions. 0aLoanszSyriazEmar (Extinct city) 0aLoanszSyriazEmar (Extinct city). 4aEmar. 4aSchulden. 4aSklaverei /Alter Orient. 4aSpäte Bronzezeit. 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh  aEmar.  aancient Near Eastern slavery.  adebts.  alate bronze age.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97815015153160 cprintz978150152180540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151530940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501515309423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501515309/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-1